Off duty süreçlerinde alınan hataların loglanması CX-IT sorumluluğundadır. Fail araması ve arkasından aksiyon alındıktan sonra failin ve alınan aksiyonun loglanması gerekmektedir.

Fail logların tutulduğu döküman : [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/16VqMEgBhaZtcTN_k-O3VvDTmmGY3oPWt17YbT1_fcr8/edit#gid=0](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/16VqMEgBhaZtcTN_k-O3VvDTmmGY3oPWt17YbT1_fcr8/edit#gid=0)

### Fail Loglama

Döküman üzerindeki kolonlar ve anlamları aşağıdaki gibidir.

*Date :*Hatanın alındığı tarih seçilir

*Customer :* Hata alınan müşteri seçilir

*Source :*  Hatanın kaynağı belirlenir.

ığı tarih seçilir

*Customer :* Hata alınan müşteri seçilir

*Source :*  Hatanın kaynağı belirlenir.

*Client Error :*Müşteri kaynaklı olan hatalarda seçilir (eksik/hatalı data gönderme, schema değişimi vb.)
*Extension Related Error :*Geliştirme kaynaklı hatalarda seçilir. (Config değişirme, geliştirme bugları, üründe olmayan dag veya extensionlarda yapılan geliştirmeler vb.)
*Product Error :* Üründe kaynaklı faillerde seçilir. (üründe yer alan daglerde I/O Control hataları, runtime/timeout sürelerinden alınan hatalar, version update hataları, ürüne yer alan buglar vb.)
*Infra Instability :* Bağlantı hatalarında seçilir. (Airflow connection, cluster error, Gurobi, Jenkins vb.)

*Platform stability* – Kontrolümüz altında olan sorunlarda seçilir. (Airflow'da bir veritabanı bağlantısının zaman aşımına uğraması vb.)

*Cloud stability* – Bizim kontrolümüz dışında olan sorunlarda seçilir. (Bir cloud sağlayıcısının bölge/bölge kullanılabilirliği, Databricks hizmet kesintisi vb.)

seçilir. (Bir cloud sağlayıcısının bölge/bölge kullanılabilirliği, Databricks hizmet kesintisi vb.)

*Severity :*Hatanın önem seviyesi belirtilir.

*Severity-1 :*  Birden fazla müşteriyi aynı anda etkileyen ve sonuç gönderme sürecini etkileyen anında müdehale edilmesi gereken hatalarda seçilir.

*Severity-2 :* Bir müşteride sonuç gönderilmesi etkileyen süreci durduran ve anında müdehale edilmesi gereken hatalarda seçilir.

*Severity-3 :* Sonuç gönderilmesini etkilemeyen gün içinde bakılarak çözülebilecek aciliyetteki hatalarda işaretlenir.

noteSeverity için daha detaylı linkler aşağıdaki info kutusunda verilmiştir.

Severity için daha detaylı linkler aşağıdaki info kutusunda verilmiştir.

*Fail Type :* Fail mailinde gelen başlık yazılır.

*Dag Name :* Fail alınan dag’in adı yazılır. (*örn. daily, rocket_daily vb.*)

*Fail Summary :* Fail’in açıklaması yazılır. Eğer hatayı tanımlayan belirli logu var ise hata logu da eklenir.

ary :* Fail’in açıklaması yazılır. Eğer hatayı tanımlayan belirli logu var ise hata logu da eklenir.

*Solution :* Hatanın nasıl çözüldüğü ve süreci devam ettirmek için neler yapıldığı kısaca anlatılır. (*Daha sonra aynı hata ile karşılaşıldığında solutionda yazılan adımlar uygulanarak fail çözülebilmelidir*)

*Fix Time :* Hatanın çözülmesi için ne kadar süre harcandığı girilir. (*formatı hh:mm:ss şeklindedir*)

*Assignee1 :* Off duty de hatayı alan kişi seçilir.

*Assignee2 :* Hata çözülürken ekipten destek alındıysa destek alınan kişi seçilir.

*Tier2 :* Her hafta product ekiplerinden 2 kişi nöbetçi olarak belirlenir. Gece fail alınması durumunda eğer CX-IT Rocks nöbetçisi sorunu çözemeyeceğini anlarsa T2-1 nöbetçisini arar. T2-1 nöbetçisine ulaşılamadığı takdirde T2-2 nöbetçisini arar. Fail mesai saatleri içerisinde geldiğinde slack üzerinden *#ask-…*kanallarına yazılarak sorunun çözümü araştırılır.

leri içerisinde geldiğinde slack üzerinden *#ask-…*kanallarına yazılarak sorunun çözümü araştırılır.

> Info: Hataların severity karşılıkları ve hangi fail tiplerinde T2 desteği istenmesi gerektiği için hazırlanan dökümanhttps://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nVLlepvDfclKpkqmu0RkM38eMtCdL6fiOE-jqgetyw8/edit#gid=1631695579 T2’nin hangi durumlarda ve ne şekilde aranması gerektiği dökümanhttps://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1vXj6HOq59Np6c4nqsT7knK7S0U-q8kaXvHMCY3fKdwg/edit#gid=0 Severity ve T2 Support için daha detaylı açıklama için hazırlanan dökümanhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1Pt7o_qiDGYc6SBa-Dh01mZp0TWzJLA1JbIt65VN-Z8U/edit#heading=h.xgrq97k2ykk9 T2 Nöbet listesi dökümanıhttps://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1TOkTX30PmPhtazUkMdZbHxDdJAsRQJDBdvu800FBFGA/edit#gid=0 (Fail Log Excelinde Tier2 kolonuna linklidir. Oradan da ulaşılabilir)

*OffDuty :* Her hata için işaretlenir

*PagerDutyCall :* Fail için arama geldi ise işaretlenir. Fail alınıp arama gelmediyse boş bırakılır.

*PagerDutyCall :* Fail için arama geldi ise işaretlenir. Fail alınıp arama gelmediyse boş bırakılır.

*DailyDiary :* Invent içerisinde 2 haftada bir düzenlenen faillerin tartışıldığı *Product & Tech Touchbase - Fail Logs*toplantısı düzenlenir. Bu toplantı kapsamında failler CX-IT nin tuttuğu fail log dökümanından toplantı dökümanı olan Daily Diary dökümanına aktarılır. DailyDiary kolonu toplantı dökümanına aktarılması istenen failler için işaretlenir.

DailyDiary kolonu işaretleme kuralları:

1. Test için alınan hatalar ve consultant ekibinin bilgisi dahilinde olan hatalar dökümana loglanır ancak DailyDiary kolonu işaretlenmez.
2. up for rety aramaları fail logları ile birlikte dökümana loglanır ancak DailyDiary kolonu işaretlenmez.
3. Bir gün için aynı müşteriden birden fazla fail alındıysa en önemli olan 2 fail için DailyDiary kolonu işaretlenir.

ynı müşteriden birden fazla fail alındıysa en önemli olan 2 fail için DailyDiary kolonu işaretlenir.

> Info: Daily Diary dökümanı https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xV0Q_gHqXp19uSQ2A2Hp_G2c7xcqrV8wjHdZIXny9hk/edit#gid=2117955484 Toplantı Sunumu https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1aCrBO427hzLAeI7VM1axCurRGwL5dY8FLxL2ui2dHUs/edit#slide=id.g102faa0196a_0_2 DailyDiary' e failleri aktaran script reposu https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/fill-daily-diary

Task oluşturmak için aşağıdaki adımlar izlenmelidir.

Jira üzerinden “Create” kullanılarak açılan ekran üzerinden task oluşturulabilir.

Project kısmından ekip içerisine task açılacaksa “Service Development(SVCDEV)“ seçilmelidir. Yetki taskı açmak için database ile ilgili yetki almak isteniyorsa “Database Administration(DBADMIN)”, sistemler ile ilgili yetki almak isteniyorsa “System Administration(ADMIN)“ seçilmelidir.

Issue Type olarak ekip içerisine açılıyosa “Task”, yetki için açılıyorsa “Permission Request“ seçilmelidir.

“Summary” alanına task özeti yazılmalıdır.

“Customer” alanında task bir müşteri ile ilgili ise o müşteri seçilmeli, tek bir müşteri ile ilişkili değil ise invent seçilmelidir.

“Priority” alanında taskın önemi seçilmelidir. (Zorunlu alan olmadığı için Medium seçilebilir.)

“Description” alanına task ile ilgili tüm detaylar girilmelidir (Link, ilişkili başka task linki, dosya, resim vb.). Taskın amacı detaylı bir şekilde açıklanmalıdır.

Link, ilişkili başka task linki, dosya, resim vb.). Taskın amacı detaylı bir şekilde açıklanmalıdır.

“Due Date“ kısmında taskın en geç ne zaman tamamlanması gerektiği bilgisi girilmelidir.

Migros için örnek yetki taskı :

### Task Süreci

Ekibe açılan taskların yapılma sıralaması

1. Refinement'ı yapılan tasklara sprint plan toplantısında story point verilir. Story point önceki tecrübelere dayanılarak verilir.
2. Taskı isteyen kişi alabilir. Ve ataması yapılır.
3. Atama yapılan kişi task üzerinde çalışma yapar ilgili kişilerden (ekip, consultant vs.)bilgi alarak süreci devam ettirir.
4. Task ile ilgili çalışmalar tamamlandıktan sonra task ile ilgili tapılan işlemlerin hepsi detaylı bir şekilde comment olarak girilir. İlgili kişiler etiketlenir. Ve task “Done” a çekilerek kapatılır.

CX-IT Rocks ekibine devrolacak projeler belirli kriterleri karşıladığında handover süreçleri başlatılır.

### Döküman

1. Proje için ETL aşamalarını anlatan varsa müşteri özel durumları içeren döküman oluşturulması
2. https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1vqrRoCjg1kL3trx3pI7puZaOcjHUlTdXDSK6igQqQAg/edit#gid=662109219  Taskların önemlerine göre dökümanın doldurulması

### Hata

1. Hata logları en az 30 gün tutuluyor olmalıdır.
2. Success oranları belirlenmelidir.
3. Alınan hatalara nasıl aksiyon alındığı dökümante edilmelidir. (Trouble Shooting Guideline (TSG) (action, musteri tarafindaki point of contact, etc.)))
4. SLA’ler belirlenmelidir (data transfer baslangic, ETL bitis saatleri)
5. Düzenli alınan bir hatanın olup olmadığı belirlenmelidir.

### Test

aslangic, ETL bitis saatleri)
5. Düzenli alınan bir hatanın olup olmadığı belirlenmelidir.

### Test

1. Test ortamlarının olup olmadığı, kod geliştirilirken canlıya gönderilmeden önce nasıl testlerin yapıldığı belirlenmelidir
2. Projede Unit Test’in olup olmadığı belirtilmelidir.
3. Load Test yapıldı mı? İlgili sunucuda maksimum scope nedir, kaç pair ile sonuç çıkılabilir?

### Handover Planlaması

1. CX-IT Rocks’a geçiş için belirli bir süre kısıtının olup olmadığı belirtilmelidir.
2. CX-IT Rocks'ın hangi süreçleri takip etmesi gerektiği belirlenmelidir.
3. Proje Ekibinden ilgili kişiler belirtilmelidir.
4. Aktarım için kişi ve oturumlar belirlenmelidir

### Handover

1. Aktarım oturumları tamamlandıktan sonra sürecin hata alması durumunda CX-IT Rocks ekibinin aranması için gerekli düzenlemeler tamamlanır.
2. Proje ekibinden hatalara bakan kişinin CX-IT Rocks Ekibi ile birlikte belirli bir süre hatalara bakması beklenmektedir. Bu süre oturumlarda belirlenir.
3. Fail logları CX-IT Rocks Ekibi tarafından tutulmaya başlanır.

Bu süreçlerden sonra Handover tamamlanır ve CX-IT Rocks ekibi sürecin sorunsuz devam etmesi için takibe başlar.

### Süreç Akışı

1. Türkiye saati ile 21:30 da daily dagi çalışmaya başlar
2. Müşterinin dosyaları 21:30 dan önce invent-alfamart bucketına tarihe göre dosyalandırıp bırakması gerekir.
3. Dosyalar bulunduğunda etl süreci başlar
4. Yeni dosyaların olduğu klasör invent-alfamart bucketı altındaki history klasörüne taşınır
5. Pre_etl süreci başlar
6. pre_etl dagi ile raw data dosyaları formatlanarak delta file olarak invent-alfamarttestbulkdata-datastore\feed kalsörü altına yazılır
7. pre_etl tamamlandıktan sonra update_datastore dagi ile master dosyalar delta formatı ile invent-alfamarttestbulkdata-datastore\master-data klasörü içerinde kendi folderlarına override edilir
8. update_datasore daginde operation dosyaları invent-alfamarttestbulkdata-datastore\operation klasörü altına run_date e göre klasörlendirilerek delta formatında yazılır
9. data hazırlığı tamamlandıktan sonra rocket dagleri başlar

örlendirilerek delta formatında yazılır

10. rocket dagleri tamamlandıktan sonra send_output taskı ile rpl sonuçları invent-alfamart-output pathine yazılır
11. Sonuç gönderiminden sonra early dagleri çalışır

### Süreç Akışı

1. Türkiye saati ile 01:00 da daily dagi çalışmaya başlar.
2. RPL tarafı daily ile birlikte başlar.
3. FC ve Early tarafı türkiye saati ile gece 4'te başlar.
4. Müşteri dosyları Azure Storage Browser'da inventfozzyshared blobuna FC için input blobuna tarih ile bırakılıyor RPL için input-2/sample_data_for_replenishment içerisine tarih klasörü ile bırakılıyor
5. Dosyalar bulunduğunda etl süreci başlıyor
6. Daily dagi içerisinde ready_to_pre_etl taskı ile başlayan branch FC ve Early tarafı olarak 4'te çalışmaya başlar diğer branch RPL içindir ve gece 1 de başlar/
7. daily içersinde rocket_data_partition dagi ile rocket_pandas için gerekli dosyaların etl i yapılır
8. rocket_pandas dagi ile rpl sonuçları hazırlanır ve rpl sonuçları forecast_output_export dagi içerisindeki send_rpl_results taskı ile gönderilir
9. forecast_output_export dagi içerisindeki transfer_90_day_forecasts taskı ile 90 günlük fc sonuçları gönderilir.

tput_export dagi içerisindeki transfer_90_day_forecasts taskı ile 90 günlük fc sonuçları gönderilir.
10. forecast_output_export dagi içerisindeki transfer_forecast taskı ile 30 günlük fc sonuçları gönderilir.
11. dc_send_result taskı ile depo rpl sonuçları gönderilir
12. truck_constraints dagi ile cannibilization sonuçları gönderilir

FlowThe Daily DAG (daily) is automatically triggered every day at 03:00 TR time in Airflow.Customer sends daily input files during the night (basic data in the first batch):SalesWH InventoryInventoryGoods on holdGoods in transitDAG is logged with the previous day’s date in Airflow.After the files arrive:Files are copied into the Azure history path:invent-afg/historyA run_date and run_id are calculated and all data is associated with this run_id.After input copy:pre_etl DAG is triggered.Raw customer data (daily or bulk) is processed with our own codes.Historical and daily structures are created under:invent-afg-datastore/feedScope does not come directly from the customer; it is created by processing raw data in pre_etl.If there is any problem with the data, an error is raised.In the daily flow, sub-dags are triggered via trigger and wait tasks:If you want to rerun a triggered sub-dag on the same day, you must go to that sub-dag’s task and use “clear downstream” instead of re-running th

the same day, you must go to that sub-dag’s task and use “clear downstream” instead of re-running the trigger task directly (otherwise you get an error).After pre_etl completes:update_datastore_regular DAG is triggered.Updates Azure datastore under:invent-afg-datastore/operation and /master-dataSome data is kept historical, some daily.Then:rocket_daily DAG is triggered.Replenishment decisions to be sent to the client are calculated.In the send_output step of the daily DAG, these decisions are sent to the client together with the previous day’s IA decisions.The results should be available by 06:00 TR time.

NotesThe Daily DAG starts at 03:00 TR time.If the customer has not delivered the input files by this time, the customer should be contacted via email to request the missing files.If any Databricks task fails during the Daily DAG:Error logs can be accessed from the Databricks links inside Airflow task logs, orBy clicking the “See Databricks Job Run” button in the Airflow UI.These logs should be reviewed to identify the root cause of the failure.Some jobs (e.g., result-output / reporting) may be scheduled directly in Databricks and not triggered via Airflow; in case of failure they must be checked and re-run manually from Databricks.

FlowTRN ProcessThe client uploads the daily regional files (EMEA, NCSA, APAC) to the FTP server at: prod/regional/upload/<region>/<date>The daily Airflow DAG for TRN is triggered at 03:15 (Turkey time), starting the regional flow in the order of:EMEA → NCSA → APACAfter validation, the uploaded files are copied from FTP to Azure Blob Storage at: inventhugobossshared/input/history/<region>During the pre_etl step, the files are read, validated, transformed, and written to the feed directory.Regional separation is managed through the HugoBossDataFeed extension.Through the update_datastore step, the processed files are written to: inventhugoboss/operationAfter that, the transfer DAGs run and complete the TRN process for that region.At 11:35 (TR time), the same flow starts for the NCSA region,and at 18:35 (TR time), it begins for the APAC region.There is no responsibility to send results to the client.The client initiates TRN runs through the Cheetah interface and accesses the results by ex

he client.The client initiates TRN runs through the Cheetah interface and accesses the results by exporting them from the same interface.RPL ProcessThe RPL flow receives data from two sources:S4 Hana data: Delivered to the FTP at 22:15BI data: Delivered at 03:15The daily Airflow DAG for RPL starts at 03:15 UK Time.This pipeline runs only for the United Kingdom (UK).A total of 36 files from BI and S4 are copied into Azure Blob Storage at: inventhugobossshared/input/history/EMEAAll files are validated, merged, and written into RPL-specific feed tables(e.g., scope_rpl_feed, inventory_contract_feed, product_timed_uda_rpl, product_destination_source_relation_rpl).The replenishment model runs using the processed feed tables.Product–store–warehouse relations, contract priorities, and freestock rules are applied.Model results are written to the output directory in Azure Blob Storage: inventhugobossshared/output All outputs must be ready before 06:00 UK Time.If outputs are not ready on time, bo

ossshared/output All outputs must be ready before 06:00 UK Time.If outputs are not ready on time, both the client and the Invent team must be notified via email.

It performs daily target calculations.Due to the client’s multi-region structure and different inventory delivery logic compared to other clients, a custom feed extension called HugoBossDataFeed is used.The HugoBossDataFeed extension separates feed processing by region and prevents data loss during table updates.The client’s TRN data refresh window is 31 days, meaning the last 31 days of inventory data are recalculated daily.Since missing even a single day in the TRN ETL flow may cause data gaps, it is critical for the daily ETL process to be completed successfully.RPLRPL runs only for the UK market, although it technically sits under the EMEA region.The RPL flow receives data from two sources:S4 Hana (22:15) and BI Data (03:15).A total of 36 files are used in the daily RPL ETL, and each file has Must or Critical priority classifications.Several pre-ETL extensions are specific to the RPL pipeline (e.g., inventory_contract_feed, scope_rpl_feed, product_timed_uda_rpl, product_destinati

PL pipeline (e.g., inventory_contract_feed, scope_rpl_feed, product_timed_uda_rpl, product_destination_source_relation_rpl).RPL includes business rules such as free-stock blocking, contract priorities, seasonal/NOS product categorization, and outlet-based restrictions.RPL output files must be ready before 06:00 AM (UK Time); otherwise, the client and the Invent team must be notified.RPL results are written to Azure Blob Storage (unlike TRN, results do not appear in the UI), and the client retrieves the output files from the output directory.Some data such as lead_time is not part of the daily flow and must be managed manually.

FlowThe daily DAG starts running at 05:00 Turkey time.Customer files are delivered to the invent-meydiageo bucket in S3.After the files are detected, they are copied to:s3://invent-meydiageo/history/{RUN_DATE},and the ETL process begins.With the pre_etl DAG, incoming files are formatted for the Rocket processes and written under:invent-meydiageo-datastore/feedWith the meydiageo_migrate_data_req DAG, files are written to:invent-meydiageo-datastore/feed-conceptualWith the meydiageo_update_datastore DAG, files are written into:invent-meydiageo-datastore/master-datainvent-meydiageo-datastore/operationcompleting the ETL process.After the noob and rocket DAGs finish, the results are written to:invent-meydiageo-outputvia the send_output task.The meydiageo_demandplanning_noob_etl and meydiageo_demandplanning_noob_daily DAGs run only on Sundays.

## Flow

The daily DAG starts at 12:00 AM Turkey time.Customer uploads the files to the inventcccshared/invent-ccc-input folder, organized by date.After the customer files are detected, they are copied under inventcccshared/invent-ccc-input/history, and the ETL process starts.In the pre_etl process, the files are formatted to be compatible with the rocket DAGs and written under inventccc/invent-ccc-datastore/feed.With the update_datastore process, the files are read from feed and written into inventccc/invent-ccc-datastore/operation and inventccc/invent-ccc-datastore/master-data.After that, the noob and transfer DAGs start running.Once the rocket DAGs finish, the process is completed.Customer results are sent via the send_output DAG.Results are written to the inventcccshared/invent-ccc-output/replenishment blob location.

## Flow

The process starts at 00:00 (TR time) when the fiba_daily DAG is triggered..The client uploads the files under the invent-fiba bucket.In addition to the .csv files, the _BulkLoad folders are also sent daily.Each BulkLoad folder contains a manifest file.Once the client files are available, they are copied under invent-fiba/data-transfer-history.Through the fiba_etl DAG, the files are written into invent-fiba-datastore/operation-data and invent-fiba-datastore/master-data.Based on the client’s request, RPL, TRN, and IA are executed within the fiba_daily DAG using branches.The results are written under the invent-fiba-output bucket.The results must be written by 08:00 at the latest.

- If any of these folders are missing a manifest file, the process fails at the fiba_daily.manifest_compare step.
- If the required daily .csv files and manifest file have been received, the _BulkLoad folders from the previous day can be copied, and the process can continue accordingly.
- Since RPL and IA run on the maps side, the branches in the fiba_daily DAG monitor the runs recorded in the database.
- Within the maps_etl DAG, the tables in the database are updated.
- The files sent by the client are stored historically in the invent-fiba-datastore/raw-data/daily-data bucket.
- The most recent data is copied under invent-fiba-datastore/raw-data/latest.

## Flow

In Airflow, the data_transfer dag writes files received from the customer to the migstokopstr/staging folder in Azure, sorted by date. The update_read_log task updates the Status column of the read operations in the Ent_Log table in the database. The next task copies these files to the staging/latest folder. (Airflowda data_transfer dag’i ile müşteriden gelen dosyaları azure’da migstokopstr/staging altına günün tarihine göre yazılır. update_read_log taskı ile db de Ent_Log tablosundaki read operasyonlarının Status kolonu update edilir. Sonraki task ile staging/latest altına kopyalanır.)Once the data is received, the process begins with the daily_flow dag.(data alındıktan sonra daily_flow dagi ile süreç başlamış olur.)

1. After establishing a connection to CyberArk, an RDP connection is made to the IP address 10.33.33.140 to connect to the ETL database. (CyberArk bağlantısı yapıldıktan sonra ETL dbye bağlanmak için 10.33.33.140 ip adresine RDP yapılır.)
2. In SQL Server, the server with IP address 10.33.33.143 is the StockOpETL database. It contains ETL tables.(Sql Server da 10.33.33.143 ip adresli server StockOpETL dbsidir. ETL tabloları bulunur.)
3. The dbo.Ent_Tables table contains a summary of all files received from the customer.(dbo.Ent_Tables tablosunda Müşteriden gelen tüm dosyaların özeti bulunuyor.)
4. Dir_Type column (Files with a Dir_Type column of 1 mean files sent from the customer to Inventor, while files with a Dir_Type column of 2 mean files sent from Inventor to the customer.)1 olanlar Müteriden → Invente 2 olanlar Invetten → müşteriye gönderlen dosyalar anlamındadır.

tomer.)1 olanlar Müteriden → Invente 2 olanlar Invetten → müşteriye gönderlen dosyalar anlamındadır.
5. The Ent_Number column in the Ent_log table logs the operations performed on that file.(Ent_Number kolonu ile Ent_log tablosunda o dosyaya yapılan işemler loglanıyor.)
6. The Ent Log table is where we can access the logs of all Ent Tables tables. The logs of the tables submitted by the customer are stored in the Ent_log table. (Ent_log tablosu tüm Ent_Tables tablosunun loglarına ulabaildiğimiz tablo. Müşterinin gönderdiği tabloların logları Ent_log tablosunda tutuluyor.)

```
Bu tabloların birleşimi için

SELECT *
FROM dbo.Ent_Log
LEFT JOIN dbo.Ent_Tables
ON Ent_Tables.Ent_Number = Ent_Log.Ent_Number
ORDER BY EndTime DESC

1. After establishing a connection to CyberArk, an RDP connection is made to the IP address 10.33.33.140 to connect to the ETL database. (CyberArk bağlantısı yapıldıktan sonra ETL dbye bağlanmak için 10.33.33.140 ip adresine RDP yapılır.)
2. In SQL Server, the server with IP address 10.33.33.143 is the StockOpETL database. It contains ETL tables.(Sql Server da 10.33.33.143 ip adresli server StockOpETL dbsidir. ETL tabloları bulunur.)
3. The dbo.Ent_Tables table contains a summary of all files received from the customer.(dbo.Ent_Tables tablosunda Müşteriden gelen tüm dosyaların özeti bulunuyor.)
4. Dir_Type column (Files with a Dir_Type column of 1 mean files sent from the customer to Inventor, while files with a Dir_Type column of 2 mean files sent from Inventor to the customer.)1 olanlar Müteriden → Invente 2 olanlar Invetten → müşteriye gönderlen dosyalar anlamındadır.

tomer.)1 olanlar Müteriden → Invente 2 olanlar Invetten → müşteriye gönderlen dosyalar anlamındadır.
5. The Ent_Number column in the Ent_log table logs the operations performed on that file.(Ent_Number kolonu ile Ent_log tablosunda o dosyaya yapılan işemler loglanıyor.)
6. The Ent Log table is where we can access the logs of all Ent Tables tables. The logs of the tables submitted by the customer are stored in the Ent_log table. (Ent_log tablosu tüm Ent_Tables tablosunun loglarına ulabaildiğimiz tablo. Müşterinin gönderdiği tabloların logları Ent_log tablosunda tutuluyor.)

```
Bu tabloların birleşimi için

SELECT *
FROM dbo.Ent_Log
LEFT JOIN dbo.Ent_Tables
ON Ent_Tables.Ent_Number = Ent_Log.Ent_Number
ORDER BY EndTime DESC

## Flow

The daily DAG starts running at 18:00 Turkey time.The customer is required to place the files under the invent-apparelgroup bucket, organized by date, by 18:00 Turkey time.After the files are detected, they are copied under invent-apparelgroup/history, and the ETL process starts.With the pre_etl DAG, the raw data is formatted and written into invent-apparelgroup-datastore/feed.With the update_datastore DAG, the data is read from invent-apparelgroup-datastore/feed, formatted, and then written into invent-apparelgroup-datastore/operation and invent-apparelgroup-datastore/master-data.The noob Dag start running

About DAG times

- There may be a ±5 minute variation.
- If there is a delay in the start time, the previous tasks should be checked. An error might have occurred during the process, or there may be a time gap between tasks due to platform instability.
- However, if the end time is extended, it may be due to a stuck task, an internal error, or unusually large incoming data.

Runner hata alınca engine.AlgoRuns tablosundan hata alınan run presetli mi kontrolü yapılır, preseti yoksa sonraki runların çalıştığından emin olunur ve proje ekibine bilgi verilir. Hata alan run presetli ise gün ve preset dikkate alınarak yeni run insert edilir. Scheduled runların atıldığı sp(transfer.InitializeScheduledRun): [https://github.com/inventanalytics/maps-database/blob/master/CustomerSpecific/CCC/CCC.Maps.Database/transfer/Stored%20Procedures/InitializeScheduledRun.sql](https://github.com/inventanalytics/maps-database/blob/master/CustomerSpecific/CCC/CCC.Maps.Database/transfer/Stored%20Procedures/InitializeScheduledRun.sql)

UPDATE engine.RunParameterPresetValues
SET PARAMETERVALUE=CONCAT('invent-ccc-output/transfer_auto_approval/',CAST(GETDATE() AS DATE))
FROM engine.RunParameterPresetValues
WHERE PRESETNAME='ScheduledRun_HU' AND PARAMETERNAME='TransferResultsOutputAzureContainerName'

## Flow

Daily DAG starts at 1:30 AM Turkey time.Customer files are delivered to the inventebebek2shared/invent-ebebek2-input/daily_data directory, structured by date.An input control process is executed for the files provided by the customer.Once the customer file validation is successfully completed, the files are copied to inventebebek2shared/invent-ebebek2-input/history/daily_data, where the ETL process is initiated.During the pre_etl process, the files are formatted in a structure compatible with the rocket DAGs and stored in inventebebek2shared/invent-ebebek2-datastore/feed.With the update_datastore process, the files are read from feed and written into inventebebek2/invent-ebebek2-datastore/operation and inventebebek2/invent-ebebek2-datastore/master-data.After that, the noob DAGs start running.Once the rocket DAGs finish, the process is completed.Results are written to the inventebebek2/invent-ebebek2-filemanager-ui blob location.

About DAG times

- There may be a ±5 minute variation.
- If there is a delay in the start time, the previous tasks should be checked. An error might have occurred during the process, or there may be a time gap between tasks due to platform instability.
- However, if the end time is extended, it may be due to a stuck task, an internal error, or unusually large incoming data.

In this folder, all files appear under different timestamped subfolders.On the daily runner DAG, the files listed in the manifest are copied to the staging area.The copied files are then deleted from the input path.When every 7 files are available in the staging folder, the pre_etl process is triggered for that 7-file batch.Once the pre_etl process is triggered, the corresponding files are deleted from the staging environment.The triggers that start the pre_etl process are shown as batch_type: partition in the config.After 14 files are completed, the daily process is triggered for the last time (3rd time).This time, the config shows batch_type: complete.With the pre_etl DAG, the raw data files are formatted and written as delta files underinvent-alfamartblue-datastore/feed.After pre_etl is completed,in the update_datastore_operation DAG, the operation files are written in delta format underinvent-alfamartblue-datastore/operation

In the update_datastore_master_data DAG, the master_data files are written in delta format underinvent-alfamartblue-datastore/master-data.Since update_datastore_operation affects the whole process, if an issue occurs overnight, it must be resolved immediately.If there is an issue in master_data, the files from the previous day can be used instead.On the daily DAG, the concurrent_run_sensor waits for wait_update_datastore_operation to be completed in the other two runs triggered for pre_etl and update_datastore.Once these are in success status, the rocket process starts.After concurrent_run_sensor reaches success, precaution and rocket_data_partition are triggered.Before the rocket process is completed, the send_output DAG is triggered.In the send_output DAG:wait_pre_optimization waits for pre_optimization in rocket to finish,wait_precaution waits for the precaution DAG,wait_rocket waits for the entire rocket_pandas process to complete.The result file to be delivered is determined acc

s for the entire rocket_pandas process to complete.The result file to be delivered is determined according to which of these wait tasks succeed.At least one of these must be triggered and succeed overnight — this is critical.If the manuel_run_control_addition task fails, it is not critical; it can be marked as success and continued.The stop_picking_order and manifest tasks are critically important.

results.With the noob_chain_weekly DAGs, IA results are prepared, and after the post_cheetah_noob_chain_weekly_forecast_breakdown DAG is completed, the send_output task writes the IA results.Following the transfer_etl and transfer_daily DAGs, the transfer results are prepared.Finally, all results are written historically under the corresponding product folders in invent-liwa-output-dev.

[Handover Summary]

[https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1TMMzRUDBoX0G3zH8Amh0viod7HLXboKc3IADIFEQFtU/edit?gid=0#gid=0](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1TMMzRUDBoX0G3zH8Amh0viod7HLXboKc3IADIFEQFtU/edit?gid=0#gid=0)

- RPL and IA results are sent to the customer through the send_output task.
- Within this task, once the RPL results are generated, they are written to the corresponding folder.
- Then, the task waits until the IA results are ready.
- When the IA results are completed, they are also written to the relevant path.
- If the IA results are not generated or delayed, the send_output task must be manually triggered in Databricks.
- If the send_output task is manually executed, then after the IA results are sent, the reporting.allocation_report and daily.refresh_tableau_reports tasks must be cleared sequentially.
- During the pre_etl stage, the folder names under the feed directory may not match the CSV file names sent by the customer.
- You can verify this by checking the following page:
- 🔗 https://invent.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/Liwa/pages/4404609451

s by checking the following page:
- 🔗 https://invent.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/Liwa/pages/4404609451
- If a failure occurs and it is determined that the issue is caused by a specific file, you should first check the email titled “Input File Control - rundate” to see if any critical issue related to that file has been identified.
- If necessary, the ETL processes should be investigated.
- (For example: the scope file used for RPL is created by Invent, independently of the customer.)

## Flow

The process starts at 01:00 (TR time) when the daily DAG is triggered.The client uploads the files under the invent-fiba-deltainput bucket.The daily DAG begins execution with the get_customer_input module.If the get_customer_input step completes successfully, the pre_etl DAG is triggered.The pre_etl DAG corresponds to the pre_etl workflow inside Databricks.This DAG writes the data to the feed folder under invent-fiba-deltadatastore.Once pre_etl finishes without errors, it triggers the update_datastore DAG.The update_datastore DAG covers the update_datastore workflow and writes data to the operation folder under invent-fiba-deltadatastore.After this point, the flow splits into three branches:1️⃣ delete_input_files2️⃣ maps_etl and markdown_etl3️⃣ noob_etl, noob_chain_weekly, and markdown_forecastThe first branch, delete_input_files, handles the cleanup of input filesThe second branch includes maps_etl and markdown_etl:The maps_etl DAG updates tables such as products, stores, and seasons

udes maps_etl and markdown_etl:The maps_etl DAG updates tables such as products, stores, and seasons under the operation schema.The markdown_etl DAG updates more detailed tables like price_steps, entry_dates, and item_season_history.At the end of the markdown_etl process, there is also a stage that updates all markdown tables and sends an email notification.The third branch includes noob_etl, noob_chain_weekly, and markdown_forecast:The noob_etl DAG triggers the noob_etl workflow to prepare the necessary tables for noob.Then, noob_chain_weekly executes the workflow steps on Databricks.Once everything completes successfully, the markdown_forecast_etl step is executed.The purpose of this step is to write the forecast values calculated during noob_chain_weekly into the database.If there are no issues, the results are written by 06:00 (TR time).

Each day’s submitted data must also be listed in that day’s manifest.txt file. Otherwise, the get_customer_input module fails at the check_manifest step.

If the maos_etl (maps_etl) DAG is waiting at the wait_for_downstream step, it means there was an issue in the previous day’s ETL flows. To fix this, run:

```
update etl.MapsDataTransferRuns

set endtime = '2099-12-31 11:11:11.110'

where endtime is null
```

Starting at 01:00 (TR time), the daily DAG begins.

After run_date and run_id are calculated, the pre_etl process starts.

Q:How do I set up a feature branch for project testing?
A:[Development in the Customer Pipeline Feature Branch]

Creating a Simple Pull Request

To make changes locally in the project, an editor needs to be installed (e.g., VS Code, PyCharm).

You can use the terminal to pull the project to your local environment. (e.g Git Bash, cmd)

1- Open the Terminal

2- Navigate to the path where you want to pull the project.

3- Go to the project page on GitHub

4-Clone the project to your local environment.

Code : git clone[https://github.com/inventanalytics/customer-pipeline-eve.git](https://github.com/inventanalytics/customer-pipeline-eve.git)

5-Navigate into the cloned repository.

The default branch will appear as "main." A new branch should be created when making changes.

6- Open the project with an editor.(If you're using VS Code, simply type code . in the terminal.)

7- Create a new branch.

Code : git checkout -b test-invent

Branch names should be related to the development being done. If the development is related to a task, the task name can be used (e.g., SVCDEV-123).

t being done. If the development is related to a task, the task name can be used (e.g., SVCDEV-123).

You can switch between branches using the command git checkout branch-name.

8- Make your changes in the code.

9- Run your pylint and flake8 checks.

10- If there are any errors, fix them.

11- You can use the git status command to view the files you have changed.

12- Stage the changes with the git add . command.

13- Add a commit message. Commit messages should be meaningful and describe the changes made.

Code  : git commit -m “commit message”

14- Push the changes to your branch.

Code : git push origin test-invent

15-Go to the GitHub repository. Click the "Compare & pull request" button.

16- Before opening the pull request, make sure the branch build in Jenkins has completed successfully.

16- Tag the on-call person of the day in the Reviewer field.

Tag the person or people with merge permissions in the Assignees field.

day in the Reviewer field.

Tag the person or people with merge permissions in the Assignees field.

The description field should include the Jenkins success build link and, if available, the relevant Jira issue link.

17- Click the "Create pull request" button and wait for the assigned person to merge it into the main branch.

## Flow

daily_runner DAGCustomer File Upload (Staging Preparation)Every day around 10:30 TR, the customer uploads daily batch files for four brands (TMW, JAB, MSP, KNG) into:invent-tbretail-input/flexible_etl_staging/{timestamp}/Each brand has its own timestamped folder.Staging CheckBefore the Flexible ETL starts, the system checks whether four complete batch folders (one for each brand) are present.If any are missing, ETL waits.Start Batch ProcessingWhen all four batch folders arrive, the Flexible ETL begins.The daily_runner is triggered four times, once per brand. 4. BackupBefore processing, each brand’s batch data is copied to:invent-tbretail-input/backup/{timestamp}/ 5

pBefore processing, each brand’s batch data is copied to:invent-tbretail-input/backup/{timestamp}/ 5. Merge & Move to History & Clean StagingAll four brands’ batch data is merged into a single combined dataset for further processing.After merging, the combined data is moved to:invent-tbretail-input/history/{timestamp}/The original staging folders are then deleted.When backup, merge, and history steps are done, the next Daily ETL DAG is automatically triggered.

# TBRental (Tailored Brands Rental)

Process Start -> 12:00Result Delivery ->Note: The times are specified in TR time.Result Delivery Schedule Results are not published on a daily basis. Instead, they are shared at specific times throughout the year upon the completion of DC Rebalance and Buy analyses.Daily DAG (Scheduled Tasks) The Daily DAG must be completed within the same day it starts, specifically before the next scheduled DAG begins its cycle. Generally, delays in this process do not cause issues as long as the task finishes before the next run.Update Datastore DAG This process is responsible for inserting the necessary tables for DC Rebalance into the database. While delays are typically not a concern, they become critical during active Rebalance periods, as any delay would prevent the timely delivery of the results.

content:
## If pipeline fails before pre_etl DAG:

- Check the file count of the raw data folder. (file count has to be same with the previous days)
- Check if the raw data folder is under the history folder.
- Check if there is a manifest file.Check inside of the manifest file if the folder contains one.
- Check both raw data that customer uploads and the one under history to make sure that we have copied every file correctly under history.
- Check the customer’s input table to determine if the missing files are critical or not. (Find the Input Tables under customers tab)

After diagnosing the error we will notify the customer if we cannot make the pipeline running with the files we have.

When the files arrive we will make sure that pipeline works with new files.

- Delete the raw data folder after back it up in temp folder
- Move the new folder under history (whether from airflow DT tasks or manually)

## I/O Control Error:

Move the new folder under history (whether from airflow DT tasks or manually)

## I/O Control Error:

The below image is a sample for I/O Control Error. If it is not inventory and we don’t have anyone to ask we will mark success the task and keep the pipeline running but If the error is in the inventory we will stop the process and notify the customer.

*Sample image is for sales*

To make sure of the error we need to make a raw data check. According to the image above I/O Control indicates that we have an error in the sum_sales_quantity column and in the daily_data table the sum_sales_quantity column is filled with the sales data. So we need to go and check sales data that the customer uploaded. In this case it is usually sales.csv or transactional_sales.csv but it can vary.

## Rocket Pandas Index Errors:

it is usually sales.csv or transactional_sales.csv but it can vary.

## Rocket Pandas Index Errors:

We have indexes in rocket pandas optimization tasks and sometimes some of them fail and we have to go and clear that index until it succeeds. To clear an index from the dropdown we need to select the index that fails and clear that individually.

*Sample image is from rocket_pandas.pre_optimization task*

## Databricks Related Errors:

Sometimes, we encounter errors due to platform instabilities. For example, the connection between Airflow and Databricks can occasionally drop, causing Airflow tasks to fail even though the corresponding Databricks task remains active. In these situations, we need to wait until the Databricks task completes and then manually mark success the Airflow task.

## Extension Related Errors (Development Errors):

and then manually mark success the Airflow task.

## Extension Related Errors (Development Errors):

Active development is going for every project, and sometimes pipelines fail because of these developments. When this happens, we first try to find the problem. If it’s easy to fix, we fix it right away. If it’s not easy, we run the task on Databricks using the previous stable version (before the latest changes). If we can’t do that either, we revert the changes on GitHub. If the problem continues after reverting, we call T1.

## get_customer_input Task Group:

customer_input_sensor:

This task waits for the raw data that customers upload to the defined storage. If this task fails we should check if customer send the data, if not notify the customer of project team, if files are there investigate further to find the root cause.

#### get_input_folder_path:

If customer_input_sensor is success, this task will find the raw data path and pass it to xcom so that other tasks can use it.

#### manifest_file_sensor:

We have an aggrement with almost every customer on manifest file. This file is the proof of data transfer is done by the customer. This will be the last file that will be uploaded to the raw data path. This task is waiting for manifest file to be uploaded. If this task fails check for the missing files in the raw data path and notify the customer.

Copy to history tasks:

This can vary, but the basic logic is to copy the raw data folder under our history folder.

#### check_manifest:

, but the basic logic is to copy the raw data folder under our history folder.

#### check_manifest:

This task is about the content of the manifest file, if the manifest file corrupted we should let the customer know that we recieved corrupted manifest file and ask them for the correct one.

---

#### calculate_run_date

> Info: This task can be before or after the get_customer_input Task Group

This task will calculate the run date that the whole pipeline will use.

#### create_data_feed_run_id

This task will generate the run id that will be used in pre_etl & update_datastore DAGs.

---

> Info: Daily DAG is the DAG that controls every other DAG. With our trigger and wait tasks, we are checking the status of the running DAGs. For example, the trigger_pre_etl task triggers the pre_etl DAG for that day, and the wait_pre_etl task waits for that to complete. In any failure case in the pre_etl DAG, wait task will fail too, and PagerDuty will notify the on-call person.

lure case in the pre_etl DAG, wait task will fail too, and PagerDuty will notify the on-call person.

After resolving the error in the triggered DAG (in this example, it is the pre_etl DAG), we should resume the daily pipeline. To do that, we need to downstream clear the wait task.
---

> Info: input_control DAG is a custom DAG and will not be seen in every pipeline.

input_control DAG

This is the DAG that we are generating an email about the contents of the raw data. If critical data is problematic pipeline stops.

---

pre_etl DAG

This is the DAG where preparations are made before the ETL process. Tasks in this DAG include writing raw data to a feed (silver) folder under the datastore according to their metadata.

> Info: We keep our metadata in Pokedex.Pokedex Tutorial

---

update_datastore DAG

their metadata.

> Info: We keep our metadata in Pokedex.Pokedex Tutorial

---

update_datastore DAG

This is the DAG that updates our gold (operation & master-data) tables daily with the data written in the feed. Every operation in the daily pipeline will use these operation and master-data tables so it is important that these are filled with correct data.
Whats optimization task and how to check logs → [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1xAe51LNA9NspVgUZBpI6twAho9Y9Kep5/view](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1xAe51LNA9NspVgUZBpI6twAho9Y9Kep5/view)

# OTCF

FlowThe customer sends daily data to invent-otcf-input in Microsoft Azure Storage every day between 5.30-6.00 AM.  Client has been informed that Invent needs at least 3 hr to generate results.The daily runner is scheduled for 05:00 AM but OTCF Daily Dag starts whenever the data arrives at every day. When daily dag starts, daily data is transferred from invent-otcf-input to invent-otcf-input/history with get_customer_input.copy_input_files_to_history task.All files are pushed at once so there is no partial upload of the files.We receive a total of 23 files in the daily flow.Customer historical data is stored in invent-otcf-input/backup.OTCF Daily Dag checks the manifest file.If the system cannot find the manifest file, it will assume that the files are not complete

est file.If the system cannot find the manifest file, it will assume that the files are not complete. If there are missing files with the Critical column is No in the following table, related tasks can be marked success, and the latest data in the datastore can be used.If there are missing files with the Critical column is Yes in the following table, you should contact with customer.

## Flow

The client places the required files for RPL in the invent-aloyoga-inputThe daily DAG starts running at 01:00 pm Tr. time.Process starts once the client files are available.Files are copied from  invent-aloyoga-input to the  inventaloyogashared/history blob in Azure. ETL process is completed with the  pre_etl and update_datastore DAGs.After the ETL process is completed, the result delivery, rocket, and noob branches  start running.. The results are delivered to the client through the send_output task, which writes them to the invent-aloyoga-output blob.

notef0f07396-f314-484c-a377-179378789fbfAbout DAG times

3. However, if the end time is extended, it may be due to a stuck task, an internal error, or unusually large incoming data.

## Flow

The customer sends daily data to https://inventbootsgrsshared.blob.core.windows.net/invent-boots-input/in Microsoft Azure Storage every night. The daily folder is of the format hardcoded as 2025-09-07T200000.000Z_01, 2025-09-07T221500.000Z_02, 2025-09-08T030000.000Z_03 every Monday night to Saturday night. On Sunday night, we receive only the first one, with _01 suffix.    The task in the our daily runner DAG moves the file from the invent-boots-input folder to the history folder.    Boots to drop data on Azure blob by 8pm, 22.30pm BST and 02.30am (next day) daily. The files starts to arrive earlier than and to be completed by the respective times. Current runtime is max 36min for PreETL, 40 min for Update Datastore, 50min for Rocket Partition for first batch

ime is max 36min for PreETL, 40 min for Update Datastore, 50min for Rocket Partition for first batch. The second batch starts at 22.30pm is expected to be finished by 00.43 before rollout which includes combined etl for 24 min, 25 min for rocket pandas, 15 min for send output (up until generate_manifest), this is an SLA for generate_manifest task in send_output dag.    The Airflow job starts at around 16:45 PM UTC every day and is expected to finish by 9.00 am UTC the next day.    The ad-hoc allocation dags are run on an ad-hoc basis.

## Flow

The daily_runner DAG starts at 05:00 AM Turkey time.Process starts once the client files are available.The customer drops the files into the input folder.After the manifest check, the files are moved to the inventfootasylumshared/invent-footasylum-input history folder and daily startsIn the pre_etl process, the files are formatted to be compatible with the rocket DAGs and written under inventfootasylum/invent-footasylum-datastore /feed.With the update_datastore process, the files are read from feed and written into inventfootasylum/invent-footasylum-datastore /operation and inventfootasylum/invent-footasylum-datastore /master-data.After that, the noob and transfer DAGs start running.Once the rocket DAGs finish, the process is completed.Customer results are sent via the send_output DAG.Results are written to the inventfootasylumshared/invent-footasylum -output/replenishment blob location.

lts are written to the inventfootasylumshared/invent-footasylum -output/replenishment blob location.

## Flow

 The customer sends daily data to invent-beymen-input/ in Microsoft Azure Storage every day at 10.00 AM ( it will be preponed later) The daily runner is scheduled for 11:30 AM. ( it will be preponed later) Daily runner triggers daily DAG. When the daily DAG is triggered daily data is transfered from invent-beymen-input to invent-beymen-input/history folder. All files are pushed at once, no partial upload 21 files + 1 manifest receieved per day. Customer historical data is stored in invent-beymen-input-dev/HISTORICAL_DATA/backup. Beymen Daily Dag checks the manifest file. If the system cannot find the manifest file, it will assume that the files are not complete. If there are missing files with the Critical column is No in the following table, related tasks can be marked success, and the latest data in the datastore can be used.  If there are missing files with the Critical column is Yes in the following table, you should contact with customer.

## Flow

    The customer sends daily data to invent-caleres-input-dev/ in Microsoft Azure Storage every day between 9.30-10.00 AM.     The daily runner is scheduled for 9:00 AM. When daily dag starts, daily data is transferred from invent-otcf-input-dev to invent-otcf-input-dev/history with get_customer_input.copy_input_files_to_history task.    All files are pushed at once so there is no partial upload of the files.    We receive a total of 28 files in the daily flow.    Caleres Daily Dag checks the manifest file.    If the system cannot find the manifest file, it will assume that the files are not complete. If there are missing files with the Critical column is No in the following table, related tasks can be marked success, and the latest data in the datastore can be used.    If there are missing files with the Critical column is Yes in the following table, you should contact with customer.

## Flow

The customer sends daily data to input folders indicating the date in format invent-gratis-input/YYYYMMDD/ in Microsoft Azure Storage every night at 11.50 PM. E.g. “invent-gratis-input/20251025/”.    Daily Dag starts waiting for manifest file from 11.00 PM and dag starts running once manifest file is written to daily data path. If manifest does not arrive in 5 hours from 11.00 PM, the dag fails.    Read files are moved to invent-gratis-input/history/YYYYMMDD/.    Pre-ETL pipeline classes    Store RPL output is expected to arrive not later than 06:00 (GMT+3). In the current flow, Store RPL output is ready by 04:30 on average, so there is around 90 minutes of buffer to fix errors that block the DAG run.    DC RPL output is expected to arrive not later than 08:00 (GMT+3). This timestamp applies for the Omega-UI task. There is no time restriction for DC RPL Send Output

). This timestamp applies for the Omega-UI task. There is no time restriction for DC RPL Send Output. In the current flow, DC RPL output is ready by 06:45 on the average, so there is around 75 minutes of buffer to fix errors that block the DAG run. As of January 2026, there are known areas of improvement in the flow that could result in more than 30 mins of additional buffer.
